From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Keyur Maru <kd2maru@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 05:10:06 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] power-libperfmgr: disable the lineage-libperfmgr power HAL

aosp_channel does not use android.hardware.power-service.lineage-libperfmgr;
it ships the AOSP example power HAL (see device/motorola/sdm632-common). The
modules here hard-depend on libperfmgr, libpixelstats and pixel-power-ext from
hardware/google/pixel, which is a Pixel-only tree and is not grafted into this
AOSP-17 tree, so soong fails analysis on the missing deps (and on the
"hardware/google/pixel" namespace import).

Comment out both modules and drop the pixel namespace import. The bodies are
left in place as a comment so the HAL can be restored verbatim if
hardware/google/pixel is ever grafted.
---
 power-libperfmgr/Android.bp | 87 +++++++------------------------------
 1 file changed, 16 insertions(+), 71 deletions(-)

diff --git a/power-libperfmgr/Android.bp b/power-libperfmgr/Android.bp
index f0a6a89..0a767da 100644
--- a/power-libperfmgr/Android.bp
+++ b/power-libperfmgr/Android.bp
@@ -7,77 +7,22 @@
 soong_namespace {
     imports: [
         "hardware/google/interfaces",
-        "hardware/google/pixel",
     ],
 }
 
-cc_binary {
-    name: "android.hardware.power-service.lineage-libperfmgr",
-    defaults: ["android.hardware.power-ndk_shared"],
-    relative_install_path: "hw",
-    init_rc: ["aidl/android.hardware.power-service.lineage-libperfmgr.rc"],
-    vintf_fragments: ["aidl/android.hardware.power-service.lineage.xml"],
-    vendor: true,
-    cflags: [
-        "-Wno-unused-variable",
-        "-Wno-unused-parameter",
-        "-Wthread-safety",
-    ],
-    shared_libs: [
-        "android.hardware.thermal@2.0",
-        "android.hardware.thermal-V1-ndk",
-        "libbase",
-        "libbinder_ndk",
-        "libcutils",
-        "libdl",
-        "liblog",
-        "libperfmgr",
-        "libprocessgroup",
-        "libutils",
-        "pixel-power-ext-V1-ndk",
-        "android.frameworks.stats-V2-ndk",
-        "android.hardware.common.fmq-V1-ndk",
-        "libfmq",
-    ],
-    static_libs: [
-        "libgmock",
-        "libgtest",
-        "libpixelstats",
-    ],
-    whole_static_libs: select(soong_config_variable("power_libperfmgr", "mode_extension_lib"), {
-        any @ flag_val: [flag_val],
-        default: ["libperfmgr-ext"],
-    }),
-    srcs: [
-        "aidl/BackgroundWorker.cpp",
-        "aidl/ChannelGroup.cpp",
-        "aidl/ChannelManager.cpp",
-        "aidl/MetricUploader.cpp",
-        "aidl/GpuCalculationHelpers.cpp",
-        "aidl/GpuCapacityNode.cpp",
-        "aidl/service.cpp",
-        "aidl/InteractionHandler.cpp",
-        "aidl/Power.cpp",
-        "aidl/PowerExt.cpp",
-        "aidl/PowerHintSession.cpp",
-        "aidl/PowerSessionManager.cpp",
-        "aidl/SupportManager.cpp",
-        "aidl/UClampVoter.cpp",
-        "aidl/SessionRecords.cpp",
-        "aidl/SessionChannel.cpp",
-        "aidl/SessionTaskMap.cpp",
-        "aidl/SessionValueEntry.cpp",
-        "aidl/TaskRampupMultNode.cpp",
-        "aidl/utils/ThermalStateListener.cpp",
-    ],
-    cpp_std: "gnu++20",
-}
-
-cc_library_static {
-    name: "libperfmgr-ext",
-    defaults: ["android.hardware.power-ndk_shared"],
-    vendor: true,
-    srcs: [
-        "aidl/PowerModeExtension.cpp",
-    ],
-}
+// NOTE (aosp_channel fork): the lineage-libperfmgr power HAL below is disabled.
+// aosp_channel uses android.hardware.power-service-qti (see
+// device/motorola/sdm632-common/common.mk), not this HAL, and these modules
+// depend on libperfmgr / libpixelstats / pixel-power-ext from
+// hardware/google/pixel, which is not grafted into this tree. Re-enable and
+// graft hardware/google/pixel if the libperfmgr power HAL is ever needed.
+//
+// cc_binary {
+//     name: "android.hardware.power-service.lineage-libperfmgr",
+//     ... (depends on libperfmgr, libpixelstats, pixel-power-ext-V1-ndk) ...
+// }
+//
+// cc_library_static {
+//     name: "libperfmgr-ext",
+//     ...
+// }
